curity/oauth2/oauth2-scopes/scope-whitelisting.md", "diffHunk": "@@ -2,11 +2,11 @@\n \n A scope is not always used for controlling access to a resource. You can also use it to simply mark an access token. There are scopes that cannot be associated to roles (e.g., openid, device\\_).\u00a0Such scopes do not have to have roles associated with them. Skipping role validation for scopes is called scope whitelisting.\n \n-If you do not want a role validation for a scope in an API's request, add the scope as `white_listed_scopes` in the `<APIM_HOME>/repository/conf/deployment.toml` file and restart the server. It will be whitelisted. For example,\n+If you do not want a role validation for a scope in an API's request, add the scope as `allowed_scopes` in the `<API-M_HOME>/repository/conf/deployment.toml` file and restart the server. It will be whitelisted. For example,", "state": "SUBMITTED", "replyTo": null, "originalCommit": {"oid": "bdab6990af0ae5ff5cb101e72e6e98fbe9bc0bd3"}, "originalPosition": 5}]}}, {"__typename": "PullRequestCommit", "commit": {"oid": "fba0e16242fc02dfc3c95985c3c62dd92dbb9ecf", "author": {"user": {"login": "ruthryi", "name": "Ruthryi Kulasekaran"}}, "url": "https://github.com/wso2/docs-apim/commit/fba0e16242fc02dfc3c95985c3c62dd92dbb9ecf", "committedDate": "2020-09-04T04:42:04Z", "message": "Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/wso2/docs-apim into master-ru3"}}, {"__typename": "PullRequestCommit", "commit": {"oid": "c99d7be9433d7804f3c7b6db1efb08cfe49e9cf8", "author": {"user": {"login": "ruthryi", "name": "Ruthryi Kulasekaran"}}, "url": "https://github.com/wso2/docs-apim/commit/c99d7be9433d7804f3c7b6db1efb08cfe49e9cf8", "committedDate": "2020-09-04T04:48:34Z", "message": "Change 'whitelist' to 'allowlist'"}}, {"__typename": "PullRequestCommit", "commit": {"oid": "5438daf03a27285d70634a5f53a0b663788ca2b0", "author": {"user": {"login": "Mariangela", "name": "Mariangela Hills"}}, "url": "https://github.com/wso2/docs-apim/commit/5438daf03a27285d70